description:
Recently sold: $355,000. A great unit on a quiet cul-de-sac.
Minutes from the Shoppes at Arbor Lakes in Maple Grove and convenient Location just of 169 and 694.

Open floor plan giving the unit an expansive feel with kitchen and dinning area flowing into upstairs living room.  
lower level features another family area with a 3rd bedroom or office space.

The unit features a heated oversized two car Garage.

Many updates including: 
new kitchen flooring and counter-tops
Stainless steel appliances
renovated deck
fully fenced in back yard
Newer windows and Siding
remodeled upper bathroom.

Recently sold: $200,000. THIS HOME HAS BEEN RENTED!! 2005 Built 2BR 2BA One Level End Unit Townhome with 1,276 square feet. Open entry in living room with gas fireplace. Kitchen with breakfast bar and formal dining room. Master suite with walk-in closet and private master bath with double bowl vanity. All appliances including full sized washer and dryer. Central air, 2 car garage and patio with yard. Not Section 8 Approved. $1,350/mo. 763.390.0437
Recently sold: $230,000.

Recently sold: $250,100. Very nice updated rambler on larger 1/3 acre fenced backyard that backs to Lions Park. Updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and updated bathrooms, newer windows throughout, vaulted ceilings. Three bedrooms on one level! Beautiful paver patio (29x16) in backyard with firepit. Tastefully decorated with today's colors! Over-sized garage (28x25) extra deep wired for 220 amp. service. Additional shed for more storage. Updated electric fuse panel. Close to parks, walking trails, shopping and convenient for commuting. Close to MTC bus parking and future light rail expansion. Don't miss open lower level currently set up as master bedroom and living/media room.

Recently sold: $280,000. 6640 Hillsboro Ave N, Brooklyn ParkSpacious split entry home featuring 5 bedrooms & 3 bathrooms.  Recently refreshed, this home features a stunning updated kitchen and bathrooms; additionally including new carpet and paint throughout, complementing the living room on the top level while the family room with a bar on the lower level.   The mature tree coverage provides a great space for entertaining outside on the oversized deck and patio beneath.  Conveniently located in a quiet neighborhood with easy access to 169,  694, & Eagle Lake Regional Park.

description:
Recently sold: $279,900. Charming one-owner residence on a 1/3 acre site.  This perfect starter home is located in a beautiful area close to parks and an elementary school.

A huge owner?s suite up includes a full, private bath, and potential for a walk-in closet, private study or office.

The lower level includes a fun recreation room, laundry and home projects area, and plenty of extra storage.  A breezeway connects the home and garage and doubles as a three-season porch.

Updates include new bathroom renovation,newer windows, furnace, central air, water heater, and concrete drive.

All new electrical, including Cat5 and coax cable installed in many rooms of the house.

Quiet neighborhood, great and helpful neighbors, very peaceful street.  Close to freeways and Downtown without the noise. Great shopping and dining very close by.

description:
Recently sold: $174,000. This could be your new home! Welcome to this beautifully updated 3-bed, 1-bonus room, 2-full bath well-lit home. Park in the oversized one-car garage, driveway, or on the street and walk up to one of two brand new main doors with keypad entry systems. Once inside you'll immediately notice the stainless steel appliances and new lighting in the kitchen, the huge picture window in the living room and the gorgeous hardwood floors throughout much of the upper level, and discover three bedrooms and one full bath on the same level upstairs. Walk from the eat-in kitchen down the stairs and you'll see a huge basement area, bonus room, second full bath, and utility room with onsite laundry. You'll appreciate the space, new carpet, and good lighting in the downstairs! 

Walk back up the stairs and out of the house and look around the property. You'll find a great lot with an oversized single car garage. Ignore the garage door in the pictures; landlord has since replaced the garage door and opener.

Just blocks away from numerous shops and restaurants in Crystal, very near both Highway 100 and 169, this location is ideal. No matter where you need to go, you'll have easy access getting there!

The landlord takes great pride in this property and is very responsive to maintenance needs.

Rent includes trash. Tenant pays electricity, gas, and water, and is responsible for lawn care (mowing in summer and snow removal in winter). Landlord provides a mower. Requirements: Monthly income 2.5x rent; no smoking; no pets; $75 application & background check processing fee per adult, prior to move-in; security deposit ($1,700) & 1st month's rent ($1,700) due at lease signing; monthly rent paid via direct deposit to Landlord's bank account. Please note: this property is not Section 8 approved.
